1. Danas *donosim* važnu odluku. (Today, I am making an important decision.)
2. Oni su sinoć *donijeli* novac za putovanje. (They brought money for the trip last night.)
3. Hoću da mi *doneseš* čašu vode. (I want you to bring me a glass of water.)
4. Kada *doneseš* hleb, kupi i malo mleka. (When you bring bread, buy some milk too.)
5. Oni su *doneli* odluku da se venčaju u maju. (They have made a decision to get married in May.)
6. Nije mi lako *doneti* takvu odluku. (It is not easy for me to make such a decision.)
7. Molim te, *donositi* mi novine svakog jutra. (Please bring me newspapers every morning.)
8. Oni će nam *donijeti* poklone iz inostranstva. (They will bring us gifts from abroad.)
9. Ne znam šta da *donesem* na poklon za rođendan. (I don't know what to bring as a birthday present.)
10. Oni su *donijeli* odluku da se razvedu. (They have made a decision to get divorced.)

Note: The Serbian word "donijeti" means "to bring" in English. The verb changes its form depending on the tense and grammatical person used in a sentence.